node.text: During our recent shoot In Iceland of the Fagradalshraun Volcano, I had a few moments to use my drone to capture the volcano from a different perspective, and in the process revealing the epic scale of the lava river that’s grown exponentially during the last few weeks . As soon as I flew close to the volcano, it began erupting... and as I began to fly away avoiding the heat and lava from the volcano, the massive lava field comes into perspective.  Click the IGTV icon to see the full video!

node.text: I am so fortunate to be a member of the TED Speaker community and was so honored when the team at TED asked me to participate in the 2020 TED Countdown global launch.  I was asked create a short visual and a poetic reflection using my photographs to illustrate climate change.  My hope is that this work will open people’s minds and allow them to reflect on how profound the issue of climate change really is.  Congratulations  to the Countdown team at TED for an incredibly successful launch.  I hope to continue to work with TED and all of the other activists in accelerating solutions to the climate crisis.

node.text: In honor of World Nature Conservation Day my Day to Night of the polar bears in Churchill Manitoba.  World Nature Conservation Day aims to create awareness about the need to preserve the environment and natural resources in order to keep the world healthy.  I was reminded of the importance of protecting the environment while creating this photograph.  The green water in the bottom of this image is the shoreline of the Hudson Bay. This area during the winter months is normally solidly frozen, but due to climate change and weeks of unusually mild weather, parts remained unfrozen. This created less ice for the bears to travel across the bay in search of food. Data is now showing that due to warmer air & the rise in water temperatures, less ice is being created and its having a direct impact on the survival of the species.  Let’s take time to reflect on the beauty of our natural world and begin to work together & take action now. @natgeo #nature #conservation #worldnatureconservationday #daytonight #manitoba

node.text:
On this Day in 1987 our first child Jennie B @jwilkes27 was born .  A beautiful baby girl she has grown up to be a remarkable young woman.  Jennie was definitely Daddy’s little girl, and has always been the focus of my camera.  From the moment she was born she took delight in looking at things.  We’re so similar in just about everything we love, she’s fueled by her passion to create and it’s led her to become a brilliant creative.  I’m so proud to be your Faja Jennie B … and thrilled to share that I’m going to be A grandfather soon! More photographs will certainly be coming :) #gratitude #blessed #beautifuldaughter 
#family

node.text:
Photo by @amivitale. Reteti elephant sanctuary, @r.e.s.c.u.e is the first ever community-owned elephant sanctuary in Africa. Orphans arrive here as a result of human-elephant conflict, drought-related issues and some cases of poaching. It provides a safe place for injured elephants to heal and later be returned back to the wild.

I am thrilled to share the new short film "Shaba" by my dear friend & colleague @amivitale. The film tells the extraordinary story of Reteti Elephant Sanctuary (@r.e.s.c.u.e)'s first matriarch. The film is now online and your ticket sales will go directly to support the elephants and their incredible keepers. It is available on-demand from today until August 31. Visit shabafilm.org or see the link in my IG Stories to watch!! 
 
#shabafilm #shaba #retetielephants  #DontLetThemDisappear #elephants #saveelephants #stoppoaching #kenya #natureisspeaking #conservation

node.text: A surreal and haunting reminder of the effects of climate change.  Over the last couple of days, the sun has appeared with red & orange hues hours before sunset across much of the northern United States.  While beautiful, this dramatic dimming is due to smoke from wildfires on the West Coast and in Canada.  Due to air currents in the upper atmosphere the smoke has blown all the way across the US and has caused an air quality advisory for some areas.  As of Tuesday more than 80 wildfires were raging across 13 states including California, Nevada & Oregon where the largest fire burned almost 500 square miles.  No matter where you live, climate change is now impacting every single one of us. We need to all come together, and act as one to save our planet for future generations. #sun #climatechange #conservation #sealegacy

Thrilled to have my Day to Night work on display in @brycewolkowitz ‘s group exhibition “Brought to Light”!!
The exhibition highlights and explores the divergent and inventive practices employed in contemporary image making today. Be it painting with light, directly abrading the negative, or utilizing computer post production tools, it is through these artists imaginative practices which reveal the far reaches by which the medium has progressed.  See link in my IG stories for details!! #exhibition #contemporaryart #image #photography

node.text: Number 17 in my tapestry series.  I was sitting on the edge of a pond in a field when I made this tapestry.  I love the textural & painterly quality that happens when all of these elements are layered into one frame.  Water and grass visually become a woven wool.  Over the last 8 years I’ve been quietly working on a series called “Tapestries” inspired by the great tapestries during the Renaissance. These photographs are made all in camera, multiple exposures & usually happen within 4-8 seconds. They are layered captures of unique moments in time. #water #grass #tapestry #fuji #photography

node.text: I made this photograph of aerospace designer & engineer Burt Rutan & his iconic “White Knight” Space Ship One aircraft for Time Magazine’s “Inventions of the Year 2004” issue.  Burt & I connected, as we both share a child like passion for creating within our respective careers .  I asked him what inspired him to build a ship like this.  He told me he always goes to sleep with a pen & paper beside his bed.  One night he had a dream that he was playing badminton & in the middle of the dream he realized that a shuttlecock floating, suddenly inspired him to create something similar that was aerodynamically unique.  He woke up and started to design what eventually became SpaceShipOne & it’s mothership “White Knight”. In 2004 Rutan & his company Scaled Composites sold this design to Sir Richard Branson who would embark on a 17 year journey to develop the first commercial flight into space.  On July 11th 2021 Branson took flight to the edge of space aboard SpaceShipTwo the direct descendant of Rutan’s creation.  Congratulations to Burt Rutan & Sir Richard for this historic achievement.  Swipe right to see Rutan with his crew from 2004, pilots Mike Melville & Brian Binnie. #time #rutan #space #photography
